//Routes are the ones that will be used to navigate between different pages in the app.
//Router is the one that will be used to wrap the entire app and provide the routing functionality.In simple words, Routes are the individual pages and Router is the container that holds all the pages together and allows us to navigate between them.
// path is the URL path that will be used to access the page and element is the component that will be rendered when the path is accessed. it is important to note that the path should be unique for each route and should not conflict with other routes in the app. Also, the element can be any valid React component, including functional components, class components, or even JSX elements.
//Router are used to navigate between different pages in a React application without refreshing the page. It allows you to create a single-page application (SPA) where the content changes dynamically based on the URL, providing a smoother user experience. The BrowserRouter component is used to wrap the entire application and provides the routing context, while Routes and Route components are used to define specific routes and their corresponding components or elements to render when those routes are accessed.